Consider the following high level programming segment. Give the contents of the memory locations for variables W, X, Y and Z after the execution of the program segment. Also indicate error conditions if any.

var A, B, W, X, Y : unsigned byte;
    Z             : unsigned integer;
begin
  A := 255;
  B := 1;
  W := A + B;
  X := A;
  Y := B - A;
  Z := A + B;
end

The values of the variables W, X, Y and Z are ___, ___, ___ and ___, respectively.

A. 0, 255, error, 256
B. 256, 255, error, 256
C. 0, 255, error, 256
D. 255, 0, error, 256

What is the result of the following program?

program side-effect (input, output);
var x, result: integer;
function f (var x: integer): integer;
begin
  x := x + 1;
  f := x;
end
begin
  x := 5;
  result := f(x) * f(x);
  writeln(result);
end

A. 25
B. 36
C. 42
D. 49
